transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra. My name is Jessie. Can I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: My name is Eloise Lovis.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. And Mr. Lovis, can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: 56359.

Speaker 1: Great. And are you at 308 Spruce Street North in Onamia, Minnesota?

Speaker 2: Yes. Yep.

Speaker 1: All right. It says here that you're looking to cancel your monthly—

Speaker 2: Is that correct?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I don't take it all the time. So I got—yeah, I got a few prescriptions over—

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem. No problem. Let me do this for you then.

Speaker 1: I'm gonna go ahead and just turn that off so it's as needed, so you can order when you feel like it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay.

Speaker 1: I'm getting a bunch of stuff. You can do that. Just turn it off for now because I already got about four prescriptions.

Speaker 2: Oh my god. Yeah, that's a lot. Yeah.

Speaker 1: To keep your prescription active, what I've done is—

Speaker 2: I've paused everything for six months. All that means is you don't get shipments. You don't get anything.

Speaker 1: You can order whenever you feel like it.

Speaker 2: However, if you don't order anything in a six-month period, you just get one shipment just to keep your prescription active, and that's it.

Speaker 1: If you're not ready, then just let us know.

Speaker 2: And then we'll scoot it down the line for you, but because you have a lot—

Speaker 1: But otherwise, yeah, I got quite a few. Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay. Okay.

Speaker 1: Appreciate that.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you. You too. Thank you.
